post_text:
UPDATE: Visit our district website for info about schedules, open house, meal distribution, and other resources. We have posted everything at the top of the home page for easy access.
-- REMINDER: Students' first day of school is Monday, August 31 and we will begin the school year Virtually for K-12 students.
-- Our principals are calling homes this evening to let you know where to go to pick up Chromebooks if you are receiving a device from the district. Please listen to the entire message if/when you get the call.
-- We sent out "Green" and "Gold" notification letters last week to let students/families know what their schedules will be when we move from a Virtual model to our "Green" "Gold" hybrid operating model.
If you have any questions, please contact us at 614-491-8044.
http://hamiltonrangers.org/

PARENTS: We are always working to serve our students and community the best way possible during this Coronavirus pandemic. At this time, we are considering distributing lunches from school buses at different locations throughout our district while on a virtual schedule.

We are seeking approval from government officials to provide this service to our students for free. However, there is a possibility they do not approve the subsidy and we will have to charge those who receive reduced or full-priced meals.

Would you mind letting us know if you are interested in receiving distributed meals - CLICK THIS LINK TO LET US KNOW
https://bit.ly/SchoolMealsSurvey

post_text: Congratulations to Hamilton Intermediate's own Mrs. Stephanie Pond on being the Make-A-Wish Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana Teacher of the Year for her efforts in supporting their program through the school's community service efforts. We are certain she would thank all of the students, parents, and Hamilton Local employees who have made this program a success over the past few years!
shared_text:
Make-A-Wish Ohio, Kentucky and Indiana
May 8 at 3:00 PM ¬∑

The Hamilton Intermediate-Hamilton Local Schools with Stephanie Pond‚Äôs guidance has raised over $6,000 for Make-A-Wish Ohio, Kentucky, and Indiana since 2017. Students and staff support Make-A-Wish through their month-long star sale campaign. During this time, students sell stars, bracelets, goodie bags, and even t-shirts to help raise funds for Make-A-Wish. Through all of this Stephanie has also become a wish-granting volunteer and has helped grant three local children‚Äôs wishes!

Thank you and congratulation to Stephanie Pond, our Teacher of the Year!

Imagination Library was started by country singer Dolly Parton and offers age-appropriate books to children from birth to age 5, regardless of parent income.

The Ohio Department of Education Office for Early Learning and School Readiness is encouraging all preschools, Head Start/Early Head Start programs, and childcare settings to share information about the Ohio Governor‚Äôs Imagination Library and encourage families to enroll into the free monthly book program.
